  "text": "The envoyproxy/envoy repository contains comprehensive C++ implementation of dynamic cluster discovery and health checking. The key components are:\n\n## Cluster Discovery Service (CDS) Implementation\n\nThe CDS subscription is implemented in source/common/upstream/cds_api_impl.h/cc with the CdsApiImpl class that handles cluster configuration updates from xDS management servers. The CdsApiHelper class (source/common/upstream/cds_api_helper.h/cc) provides utility functions for processing cluster configuration changes. For on-demand cluster discovery, source/common/upstream/od_cds_api_impl.h/cc implements the OdCdsApi interface.\n\n## Cluster Manager and Update Logic\n\nThe ClusterManagerImpl in source/common/upstream/cluster_manager_impl.h/cc orchestrates dynamic cluster management. Key methods include:\n- scheduleUpdate(): Schedules cluster updates for batch processing\n- postThreadLocalClusterUpdate(): Propagates cluster updates to thread-local storage\n- onClusterInit(): Handles cluster initialization completion\n\nThe cluster_discovery_manager.h/cc file manages the discovery process, while cluster_update_tracker.h/cc tracks cluster lifecycle changes.\n\n## Active Health Check Scheduling\n\nThe health checking subsystem is split across multiple layers:\n\n### Base Implementation\nThe HealthCheckerImplBase class in source/extensions/health_checkers/common/health_checker_base_impl.h/cc provides the core health checking framework including the ActiveHealthCheckSession class that manages per-host health check scheduling and state transitions.\n\n### Protocol-Specific Implementations\n- HTTP: source/extensions/health_checkers/http/health_checker_impl.h/cc (HttpHealthCheckerImpl, HttpActiveHealthCheckSession)\n- TCP: source/extensions/health_checkers/tcp/health_checker_impl.h/cc (TcpHealthCheckerImpl, TcpActiveHealthCheckSession)\n- gRPC: source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h/cc (GrpcHealthCheckerImpl, GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession)\n- Redis: source/extensions/health_checkers/redis/redis.h/cc (RedisHealthChecker, RedisActiveHealthCheckSession)\n- Thrift: source/extensions/health_checkers/thrift/thrift.h/cc (ThriftHealthChecker, ThriftActiveHealthCheckSession)\n\nAll active health check sessions implement onInterval() to schedule health check execution at configured intervals.\n\n## Health Discovery Service\n\nsource/common/upstream/health_discovery_service.h/cc implements the HealthDiscoveryService (HDS) which provides a mechanism for gRPC-based health status updates.\n\n## Outlier Detection Integration\n\nThe outlier detection system (source/common/upstream/outlier_detection_impl.h/cc) integrates with health checking through:\n- DetectorImpl class that creates and manages outlier detection state\n- DetectorConfig for configuration management\n- Integration with host health status to eject unhealthy endpoints\n\n## Endpoint Discovery (EDS)\n\nThe EDS cluster implementation (source/extensions/clusters/eds/eds.h/cc) handles endpoint discovery service integration and includes reloadHealthyHostsHelper() to refresh host sets based on active health check results. LEDS support is provided in source/extensions/clusters/eds/leds.h/cc.\n\n## Cluster Base Infrastructure\n\nsource/common/upstream/upstream_impl.h/cc provides ClusterImplBase with the setHealthChecker() method that attaches health checkers to clusters.\n\n## Configuration Subscription\n\nThe gRPC-based xDS subscription infrastructure (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/) handles CDS resource streaming, with both state-of-the-world (SotW) and Delta protocols supported through:\n- grpc_subscription_factory.h/cc\n- grpc_collection_subscription_factory.h/cc\n- grpc_mux_impl.cc (core multiplexing implementation)\n"
}
